history.text: Hi!
The movie is the great gatsby!
Would you like to hear about it?
yes I would
It was made in 2013
It is a Romantic Drama directed by Baz Luhrmann
And got a rating of 48% on rotten tomatoes and a CinemaScore of B
who plays in the movie
Leonardo DiCaprio plays Jay Gatsby, a famous billionaire who likes to host wild parties.
Tobey Maquire plays Nick Carraway, a wanna be writer who lives next door to Gatsby
Carey Mulligan plays Daisy Buchanan, Gatsby's former lover
Emily Foreman plays Pamela Buchanan
And Joel Edgerton plays Tom Buchanan, an upper class socialite who hates Gatsby and is now married to Dais, Gatsbys old love
what part did you like the most about the movie
I liked that it is a period piece, based off of F. Scott Fitzgerald's 1925 novel
You really get to see the lavish lifestyle of a millionaire back in the roaring twenties
In New York state
I love that it has a modern twist to it
Yeah, and the actors really make the movie
But its important to let go of the literary agenda if you have read the book
The movie had a $190 million budget, and i think it really shows
yes the actors they picked really made the movie great
The movie actually starts in 1931 where Nick Carraway is getting help for alcoholism at a psychiatric hospital, where he meets Jay Gatsby, who he states is the most hopefuly man he had ever met
He begins to write down every, which starts the movie in the summer of 1922
Nick had moved from the midwest to New york after abdonding his writing, and rents the house right next to Gatsby.
Nick's cousin is Daisy Buchanan, who is married to Tom Buchanana
and Gatsby who nick lives by is in love with daisy who lives right across  the water from them
Yep!
do you usually watch movies like The Great Gatsby
Yes, I love movies like this. Especially ones based on books and from earlier times
Me too I love watching older movies or older based movies

there was another Great Gatsby movie based on the book too,
 It was made in 1974
There some a big conflict between Tom and Gatsby. Gatsby tells Top abuot his affair with Daisy, and Tom accuses Gatsby of never having attended Oxford and saying he got his money through the mob.
Daisy says she loves Gatsby, but cannot bring herself to say she never loved Tom
They both eventually leave
Then there was the issue with Myrtle getting hit by Gatsby's car, but Nick realizes that Daisy was the driver, though Gatsby took the blame.
He then tells Nick how his real name was James Gatz and he was born penniless, and he asked Daisy to wait for him until he made something of himself
kind of a sad love story
yes
Then Gatsby is shot and killed by George, Myrtles husband, then commits suicide.
It was a really sad ending
what part of the movie is your favorite
I loved the parties
I loved seeing what millionaires lived like in the 20s
all the costumes and outfits
What do you think of this type of movie?
this type of movie is good  I like how they bring it to life
and to see the way they used to dress back then it interesting
Oh yes, definitely
